description: The Eisner Award-winning team of Brian Michael Bendis and Alex Maleev unveil a new chapter in the Halo mythos. Master Chief is captured and interrogated by Covenant forces. While back on Earth, a star-crossed human couple tries to stay alive as every single thing they hold dear is taken from them. Earth is falling to alien invaders, and no one knows what or where the mysterious artifact known as “the Key” is. The human race is at the brink of destruction---can the bravery of a few turn the tide?

Christina Baker is in the Philadelphia State University library trying to wrte her Sociology Term paper and begins to have a bad migraine. She decides to go home, and while she was walking, she notices someone in one of the building and decides to investigate it. She sees one of the guards unconscious and continues to investigate. She comes across this woman and red-skinned man doing something. Christina is then greeted by Blackmass from behind. Meanwhile, Spellcaster is woken up from her beach shore home by her owl, who shows her something. Back to Christina, she gets a headache and then the Coven are greeted by Pentacle (A traitor to the Coven) and Golem. The Coven battle Pentacle and Golem until they are interrupted by Grimoire (Blackmass' brother), who saves Pentacle and Golem and leaves.
name: Murder in the First

description: The countdown continues with a new name and even bigger thrills! And Mister Mxyzptlk explains it all! Can Mxyzptlk survive the wraith of Superman Prime? Plus, more DC VILLAINS origin backup stories: The Origin of Mr. Mxyzptlk! by Scott Beatty and Kyle Baker.
name: The Bottled Imp

description: This is an Elseworlds story set in an alternate 1962. It's dark, it's violent, and it's unexpected. Beautifully drawn by Dan Brereton and well written by Howard Chaykin.
name: Thrillkiller

description: When Arnold Burnsteel sends Scream Queen to Gotham City to lie low for a while, she ends up entangled in a plot involving robbery, ancient artifacts, and furious Elder vampires. But she also makes a new ally - Catwoman!
name: Scream Queen

description:
Overview

The first issue of this all-new series includes "24 Hour Room Service" and "A Creepy Homecoming," both written by Peter David, penciled by Kieron Dwyer, and inked by Tom Sutton, as well as "Bloodsuckers" by David, penciled by Gene Colan, and inked by Steve Leialoha. Also in this issue: "Turn of the Wheel," written by Jo Duffy, penciled by James Fry, and inked by Viscardi. Distributed by Dark Horse Comics, this is the first of the new Creepy stories published under the Harris label. This issue features a cover painting by Dan Brereton.

Overview

Will bounty hunter J.J. Jackson's untimely arrival upset Uncle Creepy's careful plot? The mansion itself tries to stop J.J. with a variety of sinister impediments, including an eight-foot killer clown. (Shades of Stephen King!) Main story by Peter David, with art by Jim Mooney and Tom Sutton. Story modules by Colleen Doran and Jackson Guice. Cover painting by Dan Brereton. Published by Harris Publication, and distributed to the direct-sales market by Dark Horse Comics

Overview

In the unsettling conclusion to this limited series, one character lives through a horrific Cinderella story, while another preaches to the damned. Seven sorcerers are thwarted in their scheme, we learn the secret of the prowling wolf, and Creepy and Eerie switch their allegiances -- several times! Can they be trusted? The fate of the survivors of Creepy Mansion depends on the answer. Main story by Peter David, with art by Louis LaChance and Tom Sutton. Story modules by Colleen Doran, Richard Howell, and Stan Shaw. Painted cover by Dan Brereton.

San Fransisco is being destroyed by giant monsters so Jack/Yochu has been genetically engineered to be a 9' tall monster killer. Jack is armed with katana made from the tooth or one of the dead monsters and is accompanied by the white-haired beauty Jill Sleet.

Overview

What happens when the premier heroes of the world, the greatest force for good ever known, become something...evil? That's exactly what happens in JLA: Seven Caskets. All around the world, things are going bump in the night. Horrifying apparitions are manifesting from pole to pole. On the moon, the JLA are visited by a pair of ghostly twins who bring a dire warning: a Chaos god is awakening at the center of the earth. His coming is heralded by the restless spirits wreaking havoc worldwide. Among these are seven undead kings who served the Chaos God in ancient times. Should the seven kings succeed in fully rousing their deity, an eternal, evil darkness will claim the world forever. But as the World's Greatest Super-Heroes split up to stop these adversaries, they find that their vaunted unity is quickly crumbling, and they no longer seem able to pool their strengths and quell their petty squabbling. The rules have changed -- and good may not always triumph against this twisting, warping evil. It appears the only way the JLA can save the day...is to become as evil as their foes. Even if they save the world...who will save the Leaguers from themselves?
name: Seven Caskets

description: The first adventures of the avatar of Justice. Women in need are possessed by a blind, sword-wielding spirit that will give them the justice that they require.
name: Hope & Dread
Love Wars part two: Operation Discord

description: Finally, the Baroness’ quest for revenge brings her face-to-face with her biggest betrayer: Cobra Commander! But when the G.I. Joe team and Destro get involved, will she even have a chance to extract vengeance? Plus: A huge twist that will shape the world of G.I. Joe for years to come -- it happens here!
name: Sins of the Mother, Part 4

description: Nearly murdered by her compatriots. Betrayed by all she trusted. Imprisoned for a year by her most hated enemies. Her only child missing. The result? One very angry woman. THE BARONESS is back, and if she has her way, the world will burn with her rage…
name: Sins of the Mother, Part 1

description: The second of a special two-part story! The truth is finally laid bare as General Philip Rey comes face-to-face with his past… What he learns may put him at distinct odds with G.I. Joe – the team he cares about deeply! Also – continued glimpses into the personal lives of the team!
name: Emperor's New Clothes, Part 2: ...All the King's Men.

description: All of COBRA COMMANDER’S manipulations cause an unbelievable confrontation between all factions: PHOENIX GUARD! BARONESS! GENERAL REY! DUKE! And caught in the middle is the G.I. JOE team members that are still standing! One of the most ambitious G.I. JOE stories ever told comes to its violent conclusion!
name: After the Fall

description: It had to happen – no one is safe when the BARONESS finally breaks out! She’s furious and gunning for everyone! Plus, more on the Phoenix Guard and their unbelievable mission! COBRA COMMANDER’s most ambitious scheme continues! And from the smoke of defeat, the G.I. JOE team strikes back!
name: What the Tables Do

description: The incredible events of the last few issues have left lives in disarray… most of all, GENERAL PHILIP REY! Sending him in a desperate search for the truth of his past, and the only person he can turn to for help is DUKE – a man that has every reason to hate Rey! Plus – you’ve demanded it: the personal lives of the team!
name: Emperor's New Clothes, Part 1: All the King's Horses...

description: The machinations of Cobra Commander continue, as the G.I. Joe team falls under siege to their… replacements?! A bloody battle explodes in an unexpected location, and not everyone walks out in one piece… Amidst all this – The return of Snake-Eyes: the commando! Plus: an angry Baroness makes her first move…
name: Take Down

description: Cobra Commander continues his machinations! The new agents of G.I. Joe prepare for a mission of unprecedented danger and controversy! Stalker, Scarlett and Snake-Eyes confront General Colton about a dark secret! An agent leaves, another returns! Plus: more on Duke! All this…and a poker game? You can’t afford to miss this issue!
name: What Lies Beneath

description: A brand new squad of elite agents step into fray! Is G.I. Joe even needed any more? Two old friends are reunited with the team! The Baroness receives a shocking visitor! Stalker learns an unbelievable secret! So much happens in this issue, you can’t afford to miss it! Oh—and COBRA IS BACK!
name: The Rising

description: A classic G.I. Joe character returns to the title, just in time to face the most audacious threat that the team has faced to date! The entire last year has been building up to this story - a great jumping on point!
name: Dark Horizon Line

description: The unit faces an unbeatable foe, and an impossible reality, in a battle that causes G.I. Joe blood to be spilled! Duke’s quest reaches an incredible turning point—has he truly found the person he’s been looking for? All this, and a member of the team quits! This is it! The last moment to catch your breath before it all hits the fan next issue…
name: Back in Black

description: The shocking storyline continues! Still on the quest for answers, the G.I. Joe team journeys to Asia, only to find more questions, more shocks and the most dangerous threat they have ever faced... When an enemy knows everything about you, including your weaknesses, is it even possible to defeat them? The pressure continues to build toward the explosive #13...
name: Reunited

description:
When the G.I.Joe team needs answers, the first place they go to is Cobra… but when those leads don’t pan out, does it mean that another party is responsible for what the team is facing? Scarlett’s shocking discovery may provide the next clue!

Plus: Duke gets put through the wringer in some horrible ways. He’s found what he was searching for - - and he may not survive it!
name: Risen

description: Still reeling from the horrible events of the past few issues, the G.I. Joe team attempts to pull the pieces together and begin investigating the theft that occurred in their midst... things go from bad to worse as Major Bludd returns! Plus - more on Duke and his mysterious mission. He's left the team behind to find something... something that may cost him his life! The intensity increases and the heat rises as we get closer to the events of #12...
name: Crimson, Not Red Enough

description: The unbelievable events of last issue have massive impact on the team! In light of what's happened, a past member returns to pitch in during these dark days... but not in time to prevent an unthinkable theft! PLUS: Duke continues to get closer to what he's searching for... and he may end up paying with his life!
name: Depth Charges

description: The underwater battle to rescue Scarlett turns bloody as the team comes face-to-face with the forces of Destro! And the result of this confrontation is the event the team never thought would come to pass... The G.I. Joe universe continues to be turned inside out with this shocking issue!
name: Fourth and Twenty

description: How far will GI Joe's greatest warrior go for love? Scarlett is Destro's captive - to save her, the team will suffer like never before! PLUS - in a 22 page bonus feature, Blaylock concludes his Zartan saga! The Dreadnoks' leader needs to secure the object that holds the key to his past - but Storm Shadow and Stalker stand in his way!
name: The Hunt for True Love; The Past Comes Back..., (Part 2)

description: The Joes have averted armageddon - but it becomes a pyrric victory when they realize one of their own has been taken captive by an even deadlier enemy! Beginning the most shocking saga in G.I. Joe history!
name: Damage Report; The Past Comes Back..., (Part 1)

description: With the Joes on the brink of discovering his identity, Vance Wingfield reaches out to a man with no loyalties: Destro! But will the arms-dealer provide him with the key to achieve his ultimate goal, or will he destroy Wingfield and G.I. Joe alike?
name: The Reckoning

description: Snake Eyes vs. Firefly! What happens when Snake-Eyes comes face to face with the man who killed his apprentice? An all-out brawl in the sewers beneath the burning city of Chicago!
name: Gangster Bang

description: Beginning a New Era of Greatness! Issue Zero gave you a taste of what Joe Casey's got in store for GI Joe, but now, the fun really begins! Cobra has been splintered...the Red Shadows have gone back into hiding...but the war has only just begun! Chicago has suffered a disaster of unimaginable magnitude. The question is, was it the result of an attack, or was it a horrible accident? The President has scrambled the Joes to find out, but what they discover will come as an even greater shock, almost as great a shock as the identity of their new advisor!
name: Shocked and Awed

description: The Joes make a deal with the devil! With cities across America being decimated by an unseen enemy, G.I Joe turns in desperation to someone who you NEVER thought would help them...
name: Peeling the Onion

description: A New Era of Greatness for G.I. Joe begins Here! "The Newest War" This is it, the subject of excitement, discussion, and controversy: Joe Casey takes on the Joes! Who will make the cut? Who will lead them? A year has passed since the events of G.I. Joe #43. The world has grown even more chaotic, and when a tragedy of mythic proportions is visited upon Chicago, the President must summons the country's greatest warrior to lead a new GI Joe team! Meanwhile, what has become of Cobra...? The answers, and the suspense , being right here. We're so confident in this book that we're offering it for a mere 25 cents!
name: The Newest War

description: Also contains a flip book preview of Re:Gex by Rob Liefeld and Jeph Loeb.
name: Secrets & Lies

description: Also contains a flip book preview of Re:Gex.
name: Something Wild

But when the kids find themselves trapped in the tunnels beneath Manhattan by the Absorbing Man, they find out what happens when the good doctor gets angry...! Get ready to go gamma as a brand-new team-up begins here!
name: Power Combo!
More Wretched Than He Who Suffers

"OOOH! They Make Me So Angry!"

description:
The next Coven saga begins with the awe-inspiring art of Matt Martin! This series introduces Eden, a powerful black magic sorceress who shares a horrible secret with Spellcaster, they are sisters! But instead of the love of a mother that made Spellcaster the white witch she is, Eden claims to have been deserted and left to learn her magical heritage on her own. She has been slowly mastering the black arts and now finally has her hands on a legendary Spellbook as well! But a time-altering spell that went horribly awry leads to total chaos in New York. Bits and pieces of dozens of time periods have all been deposited right in Times Square, leading the most incredible conflicts ever! Dinosaurs running rampant, Nazis fighting Al Capone's gang, knights attacking tanks, and the Coven are right in the middle, being hunted down by Eden!

The Coven is back, and the mini-series of the summer concludes with another issue of insanity! With one stunningly powerful blast of black magic gone horribly awry, Eden has brought the past back to life, smack in the middle of New York City! As the Coven tried to regroup in order to rescue Fantom, chaos in the streets causes more than a few delays... such as dinosaurs trying to eat Spellcaster! Is Sasha ready for the challenge of facing off against a master of the mystic arts who has a Spellbook just as powerful as hers?

In this special two-story issue, Foghorn Leghorn battles a cocky rooster with his eyes on Miss Prissy in "Barnyard Gladiators," and Bugs finds himself in an alternate reality where every character is a polar opposite in "Hare-allel Universe".
name: Free Corn!

description: Coven is back, better than ever! The legendary series returns in full color with all new art by Al Rio! Coven was one of the success stories of the late 90s and now Avatar starts to deliver regular Coven material with top talent attached. Al Rio calls these pages the best of his career and Nimbus Studios colors are rich and vibrant. This first issue focuses on the sexy Spellcaster as she must fight the forces of Hell to rescue the soul of her murdered mother. But what if the ruler of Hell has other plans for Spellcaster? A perfect new series for fans of Witchblade and Danger Girl!

A collectors' preview featuring articles on the X-Men and Generation X. An interview with writer Scott Lobdell features short profiles on the main cast of Generation X.

It also includes a two-page spread entitled "The Salem Centurion" by Karl Bollers which lists the degrees various X-Men have earned.
A smaller-sized issue with basic descriptions of the cast of Generation X, as told by Banshee.

The month begins with one of the main players in 52 having everything — and everyone — taken away from him, and ends with messages from beyond the grave that will have a lasting impact on several DC heroes. Also, Ralph Dibny's fate — or is that Fate? — is at last revealed as he solves the greatest mystery of all. Plus, more Origins of the DCU!

52: A year without Superman; a year without Batman; a year without Wonder Woman…but not a year without heroes.

Steel fights his way through the Everymen to LexCorp to rescue Natasha and secure her with the Teen Titans. He confronts Lex Luthor for a fight, experiencing Luthor's new powers in a painful way. But Natasha finds a way to use Steel's hammer to switch of Luthor's powers, the same as he did with the kids he let down. When the fight is over, Steel topples the LexCorp sign onto the street.

Kahndaq is suffering heavy rainstorms and deaths. Osiris decides to go on a pilgrimage to save his country.
name: Man 'Aint Nothing But a Man
Wrong Time, Wrong Place (Part 2): Wheels In Motion
Wrong Place, Wrong Time (Part 3): Victim After Victim
Ravish'd Justice (Part 3): Her Face In The Light
Ravish'd Justice(Part 4): The Courage To Strive, The Happiness Which Comes;  The Big Bang (Chapter 7)

description: The world of deadly, fantastic monsters from writer/artist Dan Brereton (BATMAN: THRILLKILLER) grows more complex as Jack, the Giantkiller, meets the mysterious Jill! As the fully-painted miniseries continues, two giant monsters, Shrill and Kibosh, venture outside the confines of the Monster Territories. Jack's mission: kill them before they can mate and produce even deadlier hybrid monsters. But, on the way, Jack meets Jill, an enigmatic black marketeer collecting samples of monster remains. Who is she? And what is her strange connection to Jack?

Jack is sent into the Zone on a crucial mission: to stop the giant, ape- like monster known as Banjax. Meanwhile, Jack's mysterious ally Jill has problems of her own as a determined government agent pursues her right into the clutches of the strangely beautiful, yet utterly unpredictable monster called Zomm. When their paths cross in the land of the beasts, can the injured Jack trust Jill to protect him?

The exciting origin of Jack's mysterious partner Jill is revealed! Find out her hidden connection to the project that spawned Jack the Giantkiller! Learn how she came to be stronger, faster and tougher than any human Jack's ever seen and witness her original encounters with the menagerie of monsters that haunts the poisoned Zone. It's the turning point for our hideous hero, as he must face ugly truths about himself...and about his monster-slaying mission!

The stunning miniseries nears its breathtaking conclusion! When Jack -- along with his monster-hunting companion, Jill -- encounters the intelligent monster known as Nox, he learns his true destiny: to slay his "father," Rroar, king of all monsters. Now Jack must decide between claiming his place in the monster hierarchy and clinging to his humanity, a decision he must make quickly, as the military prepares a nuclear strike on California and an impending volcanic eruption threatens to unleash Rroar on all of North America!

The stunning miniseries reaches its earth-shaking conclusion as Jack takes on Rroar, King of the Monsters! It's a date with destiny for Jack, who was bred from Rroar's genetic material to be the ultimate weapon against the monster invasion. But even though this confrontation with his "father" seemed ordained from the moment of Jack's creation, how will the human side of his conflicted inner nature decide the outcome of his most dangerous and distasteful mission of all?
Guidebook for the Giantkiller world, focusing on the anime-style giant monsters fought by Jack/Yochu.
name: A Field Guide to Big Monsters

description: When giant alien beasts attack San Francisco, the U.S. Military responds by bio-engineering a human-monster hybrid to stop them - and GIANT KILLER is born! NOCTURNALS creator DAN BRERETON's acclaimed 'monsterpiece' is finally collected in to one high-octane trade paperback collection!]
name: TPB

description: Gorilla City is missing, and the world’s greatest sleuth is on the case: Detective Chimp!
name: Get a Clue

description:
Overview

In a school where witches are a dime a dozen, you’d better find out exactly who your friends are...fast. Kim learns this lesson the hard way as she begins to discover the true nature of her witch-powers, and runs into a crowd of Salem ghosts! Kim’s in for the fight of her life…guess it’s just another day in high school.
name: Signs and Wonders Part Two of Six
